Step 1 : Add the banner image to static files
i. Place your banner image
home/static/images/

ii. Make sure Django static files are set up in settings.py
STATIC_URL = '/static/'

Step 2 : Update the Homepage template
<div id="online-ordering-banner">
    <img src="{% static 'images/online_ordering_banner.jpg' %}" alt="Online Ordering Available">
    <div class="banner-text">
        <h2>Order Your Favorites Online!</h2>
        <p>Fast, fresh, and delivered to your door.</p>
    </div>
</div>

Step 3 : Add Styling
#online-ordering-banner {
    position: relative;
    text-margin: center;
    margin: 20px 0;
}

#online-ordering-banner img {
    width: 100%
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
}

#online-ordering-banner .banner-text {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    trnaform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    color: white;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

#online-ordering-banner h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: bold;
}

#online-ordering-banner p {
    margin: 5px 0 0;
}